Aim:-  To write and execute a C program to generate the Fibonacci series using iterative and recursive methods.

Algorithm:-

1) Start the program.
2) Declare a recursive function fibonacci(n) to find the Fibonacci number.
3) If n is equal to 0, return 0.
4) If n is equal to 1, return 1.
5) Otherwise, return the sum of fibonacci(n-1) and fibonacci(n-2).
6) In the main() function, declare variables for number of terms and loop counter.
7) Read the number of terms n from the user.
8) Display the Fibonacci series using the iterative method by using a for loop.
9) Print the first two terms and calculate the remaining terms by adding the previous two numbers.
10) Update the values after each iteration.
11) Display the Fibonacci series using the recursive method by calling the fibonacci() function inside a loop.
12) Stop the program.

Program:-
 
#include <stdio.h>

int fibonacci(int n)
{
    if(n == 0)
    {
        return 0;
    }
    if(n == 1)
    {
        return 1;
    }
    return fibonacci(n-1) + fibonacci(n-2);
}

int main()
{
    int n;
    int i;
    int first = 0, second = 1;
    int sum;

    printf("Enter the number of terms: ");
    scanf("%d", &n);

    printf("\nFibonacci series using iteration:\n");

    for(i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        if(i == 0)
        {
            printf("0 ");
        }
        else if(i == 1)
        {
            printf("1 ");
        }
        else
        {
            sum = first + second;
            printf("%d ", sum);
            first = second;
            second = sum;
        }
    }

    printf("\n\nFibonacci series using recursion:\n");

    for(i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        printf("%d ", fibonacci(i));
    }

    return 0;
}
